HEADWORD: Chufa
<hw>Chu"fa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A sedgelike plant (<spn>Cyperus esculentus</spn>)
producing edible tubers, native about the Mediterranean, now cultivated
in many regions; the earth almond.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

